Question 54 A company uses 3000 units of a part annually. The units are priced as given in the table below. It costs Rs. 150 to place an order. Carrying costs are 40 percent of the purchase price per unit on an annual basis. The minimum total annual cost is Rs. _______ (rounded off to 1 decimal place). 

\begin{array}{|c|c|}
\hline \text{Order quantity} & \text{Unit price (₹)}
 \\
\hline
1 \text{ to } 499 & 9.0 \\
500 \text{ to } 999 & 8.5 \\
1000 \text{ or more} & 8.0 \\
\hline
\end{array}
